# Normalize all text files to LF in the repository.
# Without this, editors and tools on Windows may write CRLF while sources use LF, flooding diffs
# with spurious line-ending changes and making review harder. `text=auto` lets git detect binary
# files and leave them untouched; text files are stored and checked out with LF, consistent across
# Windows, macOS and Linux hosts.
* text=auto eol=lf
